sql:
SELECT DISTINCT a.name
FROM athletes a
WHERE a.athlete_id IN (SELECT r.athlete_id FROM results r);

external_knowledge:
- Top-performing athletes refers to those with the lowest average rank in each event; 
- Average performance metrics are calculated based on the athlete's performance across all events;
- Sponsorship amount is assumed to be a measure of the event's popularity or prestige.

sql:
SELECT event_name
FROM events
WHERE registration_fee = (SELECT MIN(registration_fee) FROM events);

SELECT AVG(score) AS average_score
FROM judge_scores
WHERE event_id = 1;
